Learning how to be your own best company can be one of the most empowering and invaluable tools, especially in this current climate. The good news is, we ALL have the ability to give ourselves love, joy and happiness without needing to seek or depend on it externally ?

My top 3 tips: 

1. Be kind to yourself- knowing that it’s okay even when things may seem out of your control for now. It’s okay to sit with all the feels that come with the unknown. 

2. Learn to have empowered conversations with yourself by talking out loud or journal. I talk to myself a lot. While you’re at it, see if you can make yourself smile or laugh - it is an incredible feeling!

3. Imagine how you would support someone going through a tough time, and offer yourself the same advice. Honour yourself and follow through. The more you practice this, the better you’ll actually become. Consistency and repetition is what changes our neurobiology and behaviour. 

Being our own best company can enhance our relationships with others. It can serve us when we catch ourselves feeling disempowered by external events. The truth is, no one and no situation can ever have the power to make you “feel” a certain way unless you have given yourself permission to do so. 

And in those times when you are struggling, know you are not alone. 
There are many helplines you can call and I urge you to do so. 

MIND Australia 24 hour helpline: 1300 554 660

NSW - 1800 011 511
Mental Health Line

VIC - 1300 651 251
Suicide Help Line

QLD - 13 43 25 84
13 HEALTH

TAS - 1800 332 388
Mental Health Services Helpline

SA - 13 14 65
Mental Health Assessment and Crisis Intervention Service

WA - 1800 676 822
Mental Health Emergency Response Line

NT - 08 8999 4988
Top End Mental Health Service

ACT - 1800 629 354
Mental Health Triage Service

Please share, and let’s support our community who are struggling in these times. Your voice can make a difference! If you have other top tips, let me know in the comments ???

node.text:
At Home with Lisa.

Since my house is so old and #energy infficient, one of the ways I track my usage is by checking my Avista account online.

In Washington state, Avista has switched everyone over to smart meters. When I log in, I can see how my #bill is shaping up so far during my billing period. This comes in handy during the #winter months when I'm expecting a large bill. I can plan my budget for the month around what I'm seeing #online.

It can show me how much energy I'm using on a daily and hourly basis. It will even show me what I'm using and five minute intervals.

I've recently learned there are some #appliances and everyday #household items I use on a regular basis that use #electricity even when the appliance isn't turned on. #Printers, #computers, even cell phone chargers are typical culprits.

During this #pandemic, many people are now #working from home. They may shut down the computer at the end of their workday, but the computer is still sucking in power. They call this "vampire loads."

Rather than unplugging my computer and printer every night, I got a power strip. At the end of the day, after I've shut down my #office #equipment, I can just reach down and shut off the power strip.

There are also #smart power strips that can detect when your equipment is in #standby or sleep mode and shut off by themselves. The strips are also very helpful in houses like mine. It's very old and there aren't all that many electrical #outlets. And my dining room, where I typically work, there is only one. The power strip offers me so many more outlets to plug in more #machines.

Now that I'm done for the day, I can turn everything off, knowing I'm not pulling in more energy than I'm actually using.

Lisa, an Avista customer, bought her 1910 house because she loved the old world character, some of which doesn't make her house very energy efficient. Lisa is sharing her experience on taking some simple do-it-yourself improvements to inspire others to do the same. You'll find her stories right here every Tuesday morning.

node.text:
?? Acording to Indiewire, Tickets for Christopher Nolan's Tenet go on sale this Friday.

Tickets for those showings will go on sale Aug. 21, with showings set to begin Aug. 31. Tickets for standard showings of Tenet will be available for purchase starting Aug. 27 for when the movie hits U.S. theaters on Sept. 3.
According to the contract sent to exhibitors, theaters can hold one showing per night per screen anytime after 5 p.m. unless the theater has premium format viewing like IMAX available. Those screens may show the movie twice.
___
?? De acordo com a Indiewire, os ingressos de Tenet começam a ser vendidos nessa sexta-feira.
Os ingressos para essas exibições estarão à venda em 21 de agosto, com as exibições programadas para começar em 31 de agosto. Os ingressos para exibições padrão de Tenet estarão disponíveis para compra a partir de 27 de agosto, quando o filme chegar aos cinemas dos EUA em 3 de setembro.
Segundo o contrato enviado aos expositores, os cinemas podem realizar uma exibição por noite, por tela, a qualquer hora após as 17h. A menos que o cinema tenha uma visualização de formato premium como IMAX disponível. Essas telas podem mostrar o filme duas vezes.

#WednesdayMotivation: Did you do any good deed this lockdown? Or know a friend who did? Mention your deed or tag your friend in comments below. 

Even if it was a simple thing like feeding stray dogs! Meanwhile, let us tell you about friendly neighbourhood Batman!

This guy, who calls himself 'Batman Solidario' (Solidarity Batman), has been #cooking and delivering charity food on the streets of Santiago, Chile during the #pandemic to the needy - among neighbours and #homeless people. Solidarity Batman, whips up around 100 food boxes everyday, which he self-finances. "Batman does not possess superpowers, he uses money and intelligence to help," he says.

As #BruceWayne said in the Batman trilogy, "It's not who I am underneath, but what I do that defines me." So tell us, IG followers! Were you good this lockdown? A simple thing goes a long way, even if it was just offering tea to your watchman! Share this post as your Instagram story and ask your friends to comment too, or just for some inspo as they say!

Icelandic bulsur sausage and a stew of some sort, harira soup and Icelandic ‘happy marriage’ cake. The staff @tehusidhostel were so welcoming and friendly, they gave us some tips and filled our water bottles. 
Funny story, we wanted something sweet to have with coffee so I chose a piece of cake. I’m pretty sure it was written in Icelandic so I asked what it was and they said it was ‘happy marriage’ cake. As we were eating the cake, Al Green’s ‘Let’s Stay Together’ started playing. 
Little did I know, they were all probably signs that he was going to pop the ? question the next day! 
He was probably ?ing his pants when I was joking about the coincidence with the cake and the song.

15 days, 15 crew members, 15 personal stories
Story 1 - Kostiantyn Barankevych
 
Spoiler-alert: We would like to start-off with a little success-story.
The first story that we would like to share is from our Chief Housekeeper and Hotel Manager in training, Kostiantyn (we call him Kostia) from the Ukraine.
On board since January he was desperately waiting to go home to see his family since April. Unfortunately, traveling restrictions have made this impossible over the last months.
 
“My name is Kostiantyn Barankevych and I was on board the RCGS Resolute in port Willemstad on the island of Curaçao. My sign-off date was long overdue, because of the COVID-19 travelling limitations and the long-prevailing general curfew on the island.
I am grateful to CCS that in this hard time of recession in cruising business I have a job and am able to support my family. Nevertheless, constant delays of crew changes and flight cancellations had built up frustrating uncertainty that affected my family.
My wife, being very familiar with the life of a seafarer, understands that the whole world is going through exceptional times, yet struggled to keep patience while waiting for my vacation being postponed month after month.
It got hard to answer my daughter's question: "When are you coming home, dad?"
Such as: "next week", "next month" and "soon", - were not accepted anymore, as she stopped believing those promises. Lately it was just an abstract - "One day, sweety..."
To Whom It May Concern: Please make that day come sooner for all seafarers that still are unable to get back home to their loved ones! Recognize our importance for the world economy and ease travelling regulations!”
 
Since two weeks, Kostia can finally enjoy his well-deserved vacations together with his family!

DO ALL THE THINGS YOU'D DO TO PREPARE FOR AN OFFICE ROLE: SET YOUR ALARM, MAKE (OR GO GET) COFFEE, AND WEAR NICE CLOTHES READ THE PAPER AND THEN GET STUCK INTO IT.'.

Photo by Work It Women on August 19, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'WORK WHEN YOU'RE THE MOST PRODUCTIVE NOBODY SPRINTS THROUGH THEIR WORK FROM MORNING TO EVENING YOUR MOTIVATION WILL NATURALLY EBB AND FLOW THROUGHOUT THE DAY. WHEN YOU'RE WORKING FROM HOME, HOWEVER, IT'S ALL THE MORE IMPORTANT TO KNOW WHEN THOSE EBBS AND FLOWS WILL TAKE PLACE AND PLAN YOUR SCHEDULE AROUND IT. TO CAPITALIZE ON YOUR MOST PRODUCTIVE PERIODS, SAVE YOUR HARDER TASKS FOR WHEN YOU KNOW YOU'LL BE IN THE RIGHT HEAD SPACE FOR THEM. USE SLOWER POINTS OF THE DAY TO KNOCK OUT THE EASIER, LOGISTICAL TASKS THAT ARE ALSO ON YOUR PLATE.'.

Photo by Work It Women on August 19, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'STRUCTURE YOUR DAY WHEN WORKING FROM HOME, YOU'RE YOUR OWN PERSONAL MANAGER. IF YOU HAVE AN ONLINE CALENDAR, CREATE PERSONAL EVENTS AND REMINDERS THAT TELL YOU WHEN TO SHIFT GEARS AND START ON NEW TASKS. TRELLO IS A REALLY GOOD PROGRAM FOR THIS'.

... Pic 5 of the series ... image by © Brian Cassey @brian_cassey @everydayaustralia 
David and Kerrie Varney operate the Little Morris Cafe on the Bruce Highway between Cairns and Townsville near the hamlet of El Arish. During earlier Covid restrictions, they were forced to close as it was illegal to travel the distance to their business. They reopened when travel up to 150km on weekends was allowed. They are still waiting for enough traffic on the Bruce Highway to warrant opening their little cafe during the week. They reckon their coffee is so good it has saved lives. 
Thanks to the Judith Neilson Institute for Journalism and The Australian ... worked on a story on ordinary rural Australians in business and how they are coping with the Covid-19 pandemic. It ran in the Weekend Australian as a page spread in ‘The Deal’ section as part of their ‘Covid-19 Crises: Australians at Work’ series. This series will showcase some of favourite images from that page and the accompanying online gallery.

Centre for Public Interest Litigation Union of India (2020)'.

node.text:
Court has held that “It is clear that PM CARES Fund has been constituted as a public charitable trust. After outbreak of Covid-19, need of having a dedicated national fund with objective of dealing with any kind of emergency or distress situation, like posed by the Covid-19 pandemic, and to provide relief to the affected, a fund was created by constituting a trust with the prime minister as an ex-officio chairman of PM CARES Fund,” the bench said. The fund “consists entirely of voluntary contributions from individuals organisations and does not get any budgetary support. No government money is credited in the PM CARES FUND."

Remember this #pandemic, and the economic #crisis is temporary. So don’t put your #investment decisions and financial planning on hold just to wait for the situation to become normal.

The Covid-19 pandemic has brought the world to a standstill. Probably, this is one of the biggest crises in the last 75 years. However, the pandemic is temporary and most of us are going to sail through this tough time. Moreover, experiencing such a difficult time makes us better prepared for the future. This pandemic encourages us to revisit our #financial needs and help us to reevaluate our #financialplans.

???????? ???? ????????? ????

Having an emergency fund equivalent to six months of expenditure may not be enough anymore. A crisis like this can keep people out of the job #market for a very long time and also bring unexpected large medical expenditures. We should be prepared for the worst and make the necessary arrangements to make sure we get to live our normal life.

Having an emergency fund of at least two years of expenditure could give us adequate protection to fight any future unforeseen circumstances. Individuals should keep emergency funds in low-risk and liquid fixed-income #assets.

??????????? ???? ????????? ?????

A good health #insurance plan is a must for all. If it’s family insurance then coverage definitely needs to be higher than Rs 5 lakh. Investors should consider having low-cost top-up insurance to increase the coverage amount. Further, adequate term insurance for the main earning member of the family is necessary.

??????? ???? ????????? ?????

Traveling and large social gatherings are two things that are stopped due to this crisis. Many individuals keep vacation as one of their major financial #goals.

node.text: First bank have refused to refund my money even after complaining months ago.... It's so terrible

As important business meetings and transactions go online in deference to COVID-19 pandemic, the rate of transaction failures is on the rise and Nigerians may be getting the short end of the stick. The services, especially Automated Teller Machines (ATM) and Point of Sales (POS), get worse during festive periods, as more withdrawals and payments for shopping take place during the period.⁣
⁣
The Guardian investigation revealed that three in every 10 transactions failed during the last Eid-El Kabir celebration, as failed PoS transactions were put at 23 per cent, according to the live transaction updates from the Nigeria Inter-Bank Settlement System (NIBSS). The updates, for instance, showed that about 309,016 attempts to make payments on PoS terminals were not successful. This, according to analysts, was a very significant fraction of the 1.349 million transactions as of 3.16 pm of the first day of the celebration.⁣
⁣
According to the data, the issuer banks contributed the most to failure of transactions as 68,697 of the failed attempts were attributed to errors on their platforms. This was closely followed by errors emanating from the customers, which accounted for 37,034 of failed payments.⁣
⁣
Confirming the ATM dispensing challenge, Divisional Chief Executive Officer, Interswitch, Akeem Lawal, said dispensing error is highest in Nigeria than any other part of the world.⁣
⁣
Lawal, who revealed this at the Fintech 1000+ webinar, said this was because of the type of currencies that are in the ATMs, “Abroad, ATMs dispense new mints.”⁣
⁣
Data from NIBSS showed that Nigerians moved about N30trillion in ATM transactions between 2014 and 2019, with 2018 and 2019 each recording N6trillion worth of transactions. The volume of ATM transactions with the six-year period stood at about 4 billion; meaning that Nigerians used the ATMs four billion times in six years.⁣
⁣
To read on, visit www.guardian.ng ⁣

node.text:
What precautions do you follow during this pandemic?
Her are few tips recommended by the World Health Organization:

?Regularly and thoroughly clean your hands with an alcohol-based hand rub or wash them with soap and water.

?Maintain at least 1 metre (3 feet) distance between yourself and others.

?Avoid going to crowded places.

?Avoid touching eyes, nose and mouth.

?cover your mouth and nose with your bent elbow or tissue when you cough or sneeze. 

?Stay home and self-isolate even with minor symptoms such as cough, headache, mild fever, until you recover.

?If you have a fever, cough and difficulty breathing, seek medical attention, but call by telephone in advance if possible and follow the directions of your local health authority. 

?Keep up to date on the latest information from trusted sources, such as WHO or your local and national health authorities. 
Stay safe and sound

#safteyfirst

Studies have shown that since the pandemic, anxiety and depression has risen immensely not only within adults, but more so in children too. 
Wearing a mask and social distancing is a new world in which our children have to now adjust to and grow up in. 
.
.
.

@ppeboxes can provide you with all the medical equipment to keep you and others around you safe but the most important thing that need's the utmost protection is your mental health and well-being. 
Keep safe. Happy Wednesday.

Will we be able to fly carefree in 2020 ? What do you think - Yes? No? 

For me traveling has always included the flying experience as well...start from searching a flight to airports to boarding and ofcourse the journey.

 And while I've been having an itchy feet and yearning to travel, one thing I'm missing for sure is the flight experience  right from downloading a boarding pass, to binging on those random in-flight entertainment and even the in-flight food (hah! Never thought i'd say that) 

Really looking forward to at least fly for once this year !! ?
.

.
.

node.text:
• A 87-year-old woman, stuck in Kolkata, feeds relief workers. Confined to her Alipore apartment due to reduced mobility, Kanta Devi Karnani cooked meals for lockdown relief workers.

• According to the latest reports, a drug called RLF-100 or Aviptadil from the 1970s, could prevent lung damage and reduce respiratory distress from the novel coronavirus among COVID-19.

• Chandigarh based NGO distributes books among the underserved students by opening up a small minivan library in the times of COVID.

• Organizations are now changing ways and granting 10-12 extra paid 'period leaves' per year to those who menstruate.

• Warsaw, Poland became the latest city to feature public art projects that also clean city air, as a giant mural made of special, sun-activated, smog-cleaning pigments was painted by local artists.

• An 11-year-old Nigerian boy was offered a full scholarship to a prestigious dance school in Manhattan after his ballet video went viral.

Gempa bumi berkekuatan 6,8 magnitudo dan 6,9 magnitudo mengguncang wilayah Bengkulu pada Rabu (19 Agustus 2020) pagi. Dilansir dari akun Twitter Badan Meteorologi, Klimatologi, dan Geofisika (BMKG), gempa bermagnitudo 6,8 terjadi pada pukul 05.23 WIB dan kemudian disusul gempa 6,9 magnitudo pada pukul 05.29 WIB.

Kepala Bidang Mitigasi Gempa Bumi dan Tsunami BMKG Daryono mengungkapkan, dua gempa berkekuatan besar itu disebut sebagai gempa "doublet". Gempa doublet merupakan gempa yang kekuatannya hampir sama, terjadi dalam waktu dan lokasi yang berdekatan.

KEUNTUNGAN TUAN RUMAH LIGA 2
#SOS-19082020- Berbeda dengan #liga1Indonesia yang melanjutkan kompetisi di tengah #pandemic #covid19 dengan meniadakan degradasi, #liga2Indonesia yang sudah melakoni satu laga memilih memulai baru dengan mengubah format. Bila sebelumnya dibagi menjadi dua grup: BARAT DAN TIMUR dengan #home #away memperebutkan TIGA tiket promosi, kini dibagi menjadi 4 Grup (masing-masing Grup enam klub) dengan #hometournament sistem #single #roundrobin. Jumlah tim promosi berkurang menjadi DUA. 

Dua tim teratas dari tiap-tiap grup akan lolos ke babak 8 besar yang menganut sistem grup, dengan format single round-robin. Sekali lagi dari pertarungan ini, akan diambil 2 tim teratas dari tiap-tiap grup, yang kali ini akan bertarung di semifinal. Hanya klub yang lolos ke final yang akan promosi ke Liga 1 2021. Kompetisi #liga2 akan dimulai pada 17 Oktober - 5 Desember 2020. Perubahan format praktis mengubah peluang. Tuan rumah memiliki keuntungan l4bih dibandingkan lainnya meski pertandingan tak akan disaksikan penonton.

Semula ada 6 klub yang mencalonkan diri sebagai tuan rumah: @badaklampungfc @pspsriau @pscscilacap.official @psmsmedanofficial @official.persissolo dan @sulutunited.fc. Dua tim terakhir gagal jadi tuan rumah melalui proses undian yang dilakukan @pt_lib. Juara liga 2 berdasarkan Surat PT LIB bernomor 261/LIB-KOM/VIII/2020 tertanggal 6 Agustus 2020 berpotensi mendapatkan total Rp 1,5 miliar. Rinciannya subsidi Rp 600 juta yang diperoleh saat babak penyisihan grup, Rp200 juta di fase babak grup 8 besar, Rp200 juta di semifinal, dan hadiah Rp500 juta untuk juara. Runner up dapat Rp 1,3 miliar karena hadiahnya Rp 300 juta. Berada dimana klub kesayangan Anda? Dan Siapa yang akan merah tiket PROMOSI? #akmal #akmalmarhali #sepakbolaindonesia #sepakbolatanparekayasa #sepakbolatanpamafia

Taking an ACTIVE APPROACH TO RECOVERY is one of our core values at CB Physiotherapy. We value the use of exercise as a treatment modality and an ongoing intervention, and aim to empower clients to take control of their own physical health. ??⁣
⁣
Remaining active has never been more important. With gyms and sport being taken away from us during lockdown, and strict restrictions in place regarding exercise, it is very easy to remain sedentary right now. This is having a big impact on the way our bodies feel! ?⁣
⁣
There are PLENTY of ways that we can all maintain our fitness and strength through this period. If you need help or guidance, we are here for you. ??⁣

“Life’s most persistent and urgent question is, ‘What are you doing for others?’”– Martin Luther King Jr

NSS unit Deshbandhu celebrates World Humanitarian Day . This day was designated in memory of the 19 August 2003 bomb attack on the Canal Hotel in Baghdad,Iraq. Later in 2009, it was formulated as World Humanitarian Day by the UN general.

 We celebrate this day at the name of humanity that is humans helping humans.

The World Humanitarian Day of 2020 is dedicated to the whole world which  continues to fight against the covid-19 pandemic from several months and this has been the biggest challenge to humanitarian operations among the world .

This is the time when we help others and show humanity.
